\par 
\par (2). If sometimes you dont see any changes in the Output from the Original but Sutras have been Quoted, you should remember the Dictum that Scriptures are like Rain ( shastraH parjanyavat ) which falls without consideration on where it is falling.
\par 
\par (3). If you get confused by the use of  pratyaharas like 'jash', 'khar' etc and want to know which phonemes they consist of, use }{\b\f1\insrsid12598280 'Find Pratyahara' }{\f1\insrsid12598280 
and simply enter the pratyahaara abbreviation in Encoding of your choice and the results will be displayed.
\par 
\par (4). Sutra Numbers may vary because I have exactly reproduced used the Sutra Index quoted in the Book I happened to be referring at the time. Pls. report an error in this regard only  if the Sutra seems to be wide off the mark.
\par 
\par (5) As yet their is no support for Reduplication( 'anaci ca' etc ) and certain kinds of Elision('jharo jhari savarNe). I hope to incorporate these in Future Releases.
